      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The environmental benefits of congestion pricing are not a \"settled\" matter; they are a core pillar of the modern environmentalist argument. By making driving in dense areas more expensive, it directly incentivizes a shift away from single-occupancy gasoline vehicles toward public transit or active transport. This reduction in vehicle miles traveled within the core is demonstrably linked to lower tailpipe emissions and improved urban air quality.",
